                "content": "<div class='content'><b class='title'>Tasbih & Duaa After Fard Salaat    Practised By The Prophet</b> <gap></gap> <b class='title'>(1)Read 1 time</b> <ar>اَللهُ</ar> <ar>اَكْبَرُ</ar>  <gap></gap><b class='heading'>Pronunciation:</b> Alla Hu Akbar  <gap></gap><b class='heading'>Meaning:</b> Allah is the Greatest (utter three times). (Bukhari, Muslim (I.F. BD) H-802, 1194,) <gap></gap>  <b class='title'>(2)Read 3 time</b> The Prophet (SM) used to read the following tasbih three times   <gap></gap>  <ar>اَسْتَغْفِرُ</ar> <ar>اللهِ</ar>  <gap></gap><b class='heading'>Pronunciation:</b> Astag Firullah  <gap></gap><b class='heading'>Meaning:</b> I seek forgiveness to Allah. (Muslim (I.F BD) H-1212, Mishkat H-961) </div> <div class='words-container'> <b class='title'> Literally Meaning </b> <div class='split-words-container'> <p class='split-word'> <span class='split-ar'> اَسْتَغْفِرُ </span> <span class='split-en'> I seek forgiveness </span> </p> <p class='split-word'> <span class='split-ar'> اللهِ </span> <span class='split-en'> to Allah </span> </p> </div> </div>"
